http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/Women-join-APGV-Bank-employees%E2%80%99-hunger-strike/article13987711.ece

Women employees of the Andhra Pradesh Grameena Vikas Bank took part in the last day of the relay hunger strike here on Thursday.General secretary of Andhra Pradesh Grameena Vikas Bank Employees Union K. Bikshamaiah said that as part of the relay hunger strike on the 11th day, women employees took part in it.He said they submitted a charter of demands to the management but in vain.The employees have been demanding restoration of gradual increments to newly recruited officer assistants, reimbursement of conveyance bills, equal pay scales on par with employees of commercial banks, enhancement of wages to a minimum of Rs.15,000 per month to daily wage employees, and to make the Andhra Pradesh Grameena Vikas Bank an associate member in Indian Banks Association.Mr. Bikshamaiah said they are also demanding low interest loans to employees, sabbatical leave to women employees and officers as per Central Government guidelines.“Though the bank made an impressive growth, the employees are not getting the benefits,” he said.The Supreme Court had ordered the management to ensure equal pay and allowances to Grameena Bank employees on par with other commercial banks, but in vain, he said.